==English==

===Pronunciation===
*tûrm, /tɜː(r)m/, /t3:(r)m/
*:'''Rhymes''': [[Rhymes:English:-ɜː(r)m|-ɜː(r)m]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A [[limitation]], [[restriction]] or [[regulation]].
#: ''terms and conditions''
# A [[word]] or [[phrase]], especially one from a [[specialise]]d area of knowledge.
# [[relation|Relations]] among people.
#: ''We are on friendly terms with each other.''
# A [[part]] of a [[year]], especially one of the three parts of an [[academic year]] in [[Britain]]; [[Michælmas term]], [[Lent term]] or [[Easter term]], the equivalent to the American [[semester]].
# {{math}} One of the [[addend]]s in a [[sum]]: ''All of these terms cancel out.''
# a [[duration]] of a set [[length]].
#:He was [[sentenced]] to a '''term''' of six years in [[prison]].
